<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">06 — Frequently Asked Questions</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">California appliance repair registration — what homeowners ask us</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What is BHGS and why does it matter for appliance repair?</h3>
        <p>BHGS is the California Bureau of Household Goods and Services — part of the Department of Consumer Affairs. They require and regulate registration for appliance repair businesses in California. Registration means the company has been verified, is subject to state oversight, and can be reported to BHGS if something goes wrong. Our registration number is #A49573.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How do I verify that Same Day Appliance Repair is registered?</h3>
        <p>Go to bhgs.dca.ca.gov/enforcement/lookup.shtml and search for registration number A49573. You'll see our business name, current registration status, and expiration date. Takes 30 seconds.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Is BHGS registration the same as a CSLB contractor license?</h3>
        <p>No — these are completely different credentials from different agencies. BHGS registration is specifically for appliance repair businesses. A CSLB C-61/D-21 license is for contractors performing certain construction-type work. The correct credential for appliance repair in California is BHGS registration. Some companies incorrectly call their BHGS registration a "CSLB license."</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What happens to my warranty if I use an unregistered company?</h3>
        <p>Many manufacturers require repairs to be performed by registered service providers to maintain warranty validity. Repairs by unregistered technicians can void your manufacturer's warranty. This is particularly significant for newer appliances, luxury brands, and any appliance still within the standard warranty period.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Does BHGS registration cover commercial appliance repair?</h3>
        <p>Yes. Our BHGS registration #A49573 covers both residential and commercial appliance repair — from household washers and refrigerators to commercial walk-in coolers, commercial dishwashers, and commercial cooking equipment.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What other credentials does Same Day Appliance Repair hold?</h3>
        <p>In addition to BHGS registration #A49573: EPA-608 certification for refrigerant work (federal requirement), full liability insurance, background-checked technicians, BBB A+ accreditation, and OSHA safety training. See our credentials pages for details on each.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

